      <div class="msgContentFrame">So, open beta has come, and I've finally got a spot.  Mining is my first adventure.  I'm a lvl 11 miner now, thanks in large part to levequests and the ridiculous amount of mining experience you can get doing them.  I have done some exploring, but have yet to find anything greater than a level one node.  Here are a few observations. <br /> <br />1) A node has a set amount of charges, I don't know what the charges are, but it appears to me to be between 20 and 40. <br /> <br />2) At level 11 mining I can make six attempts to gather resources from a particular node (lvl 1) <br /> <br />3) At level 10 I learned sharp vision, but I cannot equip the skill.  I assume it is passive, but don't know how to see a list of all my abilities, including the passive ones.  If anyone could explain where to find that information, I'll see if I can confirm. <br /> <br />4) Lay of the land informs you if there is a node within 400 yalms (basically a yard) and if there is which direction you should head to find it.   <br /> <br />5) Prospect will give you a speed boost if there is not a mine within 200 yalms.  The speed boost lasts 30 seconds, and you can cover roughly 200 yalms of distance while it is active.  Prospect is keyed towards certain levels of nodes.  If you are in an area that has level 3 nodes, and your prospect is level 2, then it will tell you simply that there does not appear to be any mining nodes level 2 or below in the area, and you will not receive the speed boost.  You cannot receive the speed boost in town due to this either. <br /> <br />6) Different areas have different things you can mine up.  I started in Uldah and was there through level 9.  Fire crystals were the only type of crystal I could mine up.  Yellow Copper Ore, Copper Ore, Tin Ore, Lightning Stones, and Fire Stones were all available.  I made the run to Limsa Lominsa (and was able to do the starting mining levequests there as well) and found that I could now dig up Wind Crystals, Sea Sand, Shells, Water Stones, and Limonite.  None of these were available around Uldah.  These were all level one nodes. <br /> <br />7) When playing the minigame I have not found that there is a set &quot;depth&quot; of mining that is best to get ores as opposed to the less valuable finds.  However, each particular node does seem to have a depth value that gives better finds.  Once I get an ore I usually stay at that particular depth and finish off my swings at the node there. <br /> <br />8) In the second part of the minigame where you determine your swing strength there are three sweet spots.  (There are actually six, I believe, but three will suffice for the explanation).  These are given value by the different style of swing your character makes and each is located within its particular &quot;third&quot; of the expanding and contracting circle.  The best way I've found to not fail on the extraction is to start on one end of the circle, and make your way to the other if necessary.  I always start on the weak strike end, because I seem to find that it is more commonly the right end to be on. <br /> <br />9) The game gives you between 3 and 4 swings to come up with your prize and gives you hints after each swing.  I apologize, I'm writing this while the server is down, so the hints I list here will be the spirit of the hint given to you by the game, not the hint verbatim. <br />          1) You feel nothing promising. <br />This means move to the next swing value, for me I move from the weakest swing to medium swing.  It could be one swing value away, or two. <br />          2) You are closer/further from your target <br />You are closer means that you're traveling in the right direction, but you need to move to the last swing value.  You are further means you went the wrong way.  This can sometimes happen when you don't expect it and typically if you're following my progression means that the sweet spot value will either by as hard of a swing as you can make it, or as weak of a swing as you can make it, depending on the direction needed. <br />          2) You feel something promising. <br />This means that you are within a swing value's distance of your prize.  And this is where the 6 sweet spots come into play.  Each swing value seems to have 2 sweet spots within it, one on the weak end and one on the strong end.  When you get this hint, say on the weak end of swing value 2, then your sweet spot will either be the strong end of swing value 2, or the strong end of swing value 1. <br />          3) You almost had it, but could not extract <br />This simply means that you were VERY close to successfully extracting.  The good thing about this message is that it seems to widen the sweet spot.  Don't guess if you need to swing harder or softer, just swing where you swung before.  I've yet to fail to extract if I do this. <br /> <br />Hope all these hints help.  If I ever find a level 2 node I'll let you all have an update! <br /></div>
